public field: can be accessed by anyone
usage: used when declaring a method that interacts with users.

private field: can only be access with in the declared class/method
usage: used when declaring variables within a class that does not need to interact directly with users

static field: can be accessed with out a specific instance of an object
usage: used when a method or variable does not depend on an instance of an object

final field: can only be set once during initial declration and cannot be changed
usage: used when declaring an unchanging constant variable